sentences: Robert Roland Chudnick (September 27, 1927 – May 27, 1994), known professionally as Red Rodney, was an American jazz trumpeter.
Robert Roland Chudnick (September 27, 1927 – May 27, 1994), known professionally as Red Rodney, was an American jazz trumpeter.
Robert Roland Chudnick (September 27, 1927 – May 27, 1994), known professionally as Red Rodney, was an American jazz trumpeter.
and was a member of the band from 1949 to 1951.
During the 1950s, he worked as a bandleader in Philadelphia and recorded with Ira Sullivan.
During 1969, Rodney played in Las Vegas with fellow Woody Herman colleague, trombonist Bill Harris, as part of the Flamingo casino house band led by Russ Black.
In the early 1970s he was bankrupted by medical costs following a stroke.
In 1975 he was incarcerated in Sandstone, Minnesota for drug offenses.
From 1980 to 1982, Rodney made five albums with Sullivan.
He continued to work and record into the 1990s.
He provided an early showcase for saxophonist Chris Potter, who was a member of his group and only 19 years old when Rodney recorded Red Alert in late 1990.

Rodney died on May 27, 1994, from lung cancer.
